employment.description_of_duties:
Designed overall strategy, values, culture and management of the Unit and developed and implemented Monitoring, Evaluation and Learning (MEL) strategy for the Agricultural Transformation Agenda of the Country;
Provide technical training for staff of the Agency and Ministry of Agriculture, Ministry of Trade and Industry on planning & M&E of the transformation agenda
Closely worked with Ministry of Trade and Ministry of Industry to identify systemic bottlenecks in the sectors, formulate and implement transformation agenda to address them
Regularly supervised, mentored and coach senior management and M&E staff, as well as develop and implement the Monitoring and Evaluation work plan of the Agency;
Lead the designing of over 170 transformation interventions in the Trade, industry, Agriculture & Natural Resource Management sectors
Lead a Performance Management Unit (PMU) to design a project planning, monitoring & evaluation system, including developing and rolling out a guideline and accompanying tools to facilitate project designing, concept note and proposal evaluation as well as M&E of the Trade, industry, Agriculture and livestock transformation initiatives in Ethiopia
Lead the designing and implementation of Online Milestone Tracking System to facilitate performance monitoring and reporting from different government ministries implementing the agricultural transformation agenda to the agricultural transformation council & Parliament
Created awareness on monitoring, learning and evaluation around staff and senior management of the Agency and partners, organized and delivered training on planning, monitoring, evaluation and learning for government partners including training on Effective planning and Reporting to Support Senior Decision Makers from Oromia President Office, Oromia Planning Commission, Oromia Bureau of Agriculture and Natural Resources & Ministry of Education Planning and M&E staff.
Led strategic annual result based planning, gender mainstreaming and programming process;
Develop monitoring and evaluation framework, indicators, baseline and targets to monitor and evaluate progress and ensure integration of gender and youth issues in the agricultural transformation agenda and ATA projects;
Regularly collect, synthesize, analyse quantitative and qualitative data to report progress periodically to the Parliament and Agricultural Transformation Council which is Chaired by the Prime Minster;
Develop planning, monitoring & evaluation systems and tools to work collaboratively with government;

Served as focal person for Monitoring & Evaluation and aid effectiveness in the EU Delegation, including managing relations with other donors, EU member states and the government.
Design monitoring system for the EUD, create linkage with programme formulation and support alignment and harmonization with implementing partners & EU member states;
Actively participated and supported the designing of 10th and 11th EDF Country Strategy Paper for EU-Ethiopia cooperation 2008 to 2013 and 2014 to 2020 respectively, including for the economic sectors, private sector development & trade facilitation programs
coordinated the monitoring and evaluation of EU flagship programs on CSF I and II, livestock, sector support in transport, coffee improvement program IV and others
coordinate the internal and external monitoring of over 25 EU funded projects and programs in the field of private sector development, trade facilitation, food security, environment and natural resources management, every year including facilitating and supporting the external ROM mission
Developed and maintained the EUD monitoring system including: monitoring strategy (internal and external), monitoring processes and procedures (methodologies, checklists, tools, indicators and practices for quality monitoring, monitoring plans etc.;
Reviewed the quality and relevance of monitoring systems applied by implementing partners, implementing EU projects in the field of private sector development, trade, agriculture, food security, natural resource management and EU Environment Facility, and provided recommendations. Reviewed progress made on different key indicators for programmes and projects
Documented best practices on programme/ project implementation funded by the EUD and other donors.
Maintained the Joint Result Oriented Monitoring System-Ethiopia (JROM-E) and produce progress reports.
Reviewed the external Result Oriented Monitoring (ROM) method and incorporate lesson to the Joint Result Oriented Monitoring (JROM) system with the view of harmonizing systems;
Harmonized and linked monitoring systems of the EUD with implementing partners including the UNDP and especially with the government, and eventually with EU member states and agencies (EU Road map);

Light Review of UN Joint Flagship Programmes in Ethiopia:
design of the light review methodology;
review of relevant background documents on UN Flagship programmes;
planning and scheduling of field missions in four regions: Afar, Gambela, Amhara, Oromiya
in collaboration with the review team and sampling of stakeholders to interview in partnership with the UN Regional office;
conduct of interviews, focus groups or small group discussions, using relevant interview protocols for each type of respondent; and,
support in data analysis and final report writing.

Project evaluation & Monitoring Evaluation trainings provided for civil society organisations:
Developed and implemented business development plan & strategy
May 2013, Final Evaluation of Gewata Rural Development Program, for World Vision Ethiopia;
October 2011. Intermediate Result Assessment of Productive Safety Net Program-Plus Project in 12 Woredas of Tigray, Amhara, SNNPR & Oromiya Regions, implemented by a Consortium of 5 NGOs led by CARE-Ethiopia
August 2012, Final Evaluation of Dembia & Sokoru Rural Development Programs for World Vision Ethiopia;
April 2008, Final Evaluation of West Hararghe Livelihood Project for International Rescue Committee-Ethiopia;
Training of Trainers on Participatory, Result Based M&E for GOAL-Ethiopia.

Support the development and M&E of the organisations' programmes, including leading on both planning activities & development of funding applications, developing planning timelines, Monitoring and Evaluation of programmes/projects..
Design & implement M&E systems using participatory & standard approach to assess implementation & impact;
Carry out annual participatory impact assessment;
Carry out internal reviews & evaluations and support external evaluations/reviews;
Support provision of accurate information on project achievements & impact, quality of implementation.
Develop regular contextual analysis & inform advocacy position;
Regularly visit projects in Participatory Forest Management & review the monitoring systems in place, advising on progress & identifying best practices;
Coordinate M&E and policy related capacity building activities & ensure the integration of the skills & knowledge acquired into the projects;
Develop advocacy strategies and action plans based on lessons learned.

Technical Management and Coordination of  programme/projects  to fulfil the organization's vision.
Play active role in overall programme and strategy development of the organization in general.
Actively led the designing of gender and HIV mainstreaming guidelines with specific focus on mainstreaming in agricultural cooperatives
Prepare annual plans and budgets and strategic plans for the project work and ensure their proper execution;
Supervision and guidance to the project staff in properly implementing project activities;
Collect and analyse relevant data to monitor and evaluate project activities;
Supervise that financial systems were consistent with the organization's financial planning and reporting requirements;
Prepare quarterly, half yearly and annual reports on all aspects of the organization activities in the project and ensure that the appropriate reports are submitted timely;
Represent the organization in the project operational area and ensure the maintenance of optimum relations at all levels with other CSOs as well as the local Government Organizations.

IFAD-FFS-Ethiopia Project
Provide technical input for the preparation and consecutive refinement of the FFS curriculum and designing of field experiments;
Provide training on principles of FFS and community participation techniques and facilitation skills for farmer facilitators;
Conduct participatory monitoring and evaluation of the FFS activities;
Prepare periodical and analytical reports and publish experience

Gidan Integrated Rural Development Programme: Technical Management of agronomic programme component.
Supported strategy development and design of activities to be conducted with in the programme area;
Plan/ design and supervise the implementation of activities related to agronomic trials and farmers research;
Conduct baseline survey within project sites and organize information to be used during project implementation and also as a basis for focus and refinement of the implementation of project activities.

Project acquisition
• Market analysis and opportunity identification;
• Networking and proactive and strategic collaboration with donors, clients and experts;
• Evaluation of project opportunities on the basis of key figures and contextual information.
• Organizing and conducting fact-finding missions, capture planning and strategy preparation;
• Conceptual and methodical preparation of "pre-qualification" documents
• Bid preparation and bid management of technical proposals for key tenders including but not limited to EU service contracts;
• As part of bid management, coordination of the bid team and identification of partners and experts together with the recruitment team, drafting and editing assigned sections of the technical offer, supervision and management of external consultants and proposal writers, project design and budget development in close coordination with the finance team;
• quality assurance and timely approvals for bid development and submission

Project management and backstopping
• Backstopping of projects in accordance with GIZ policies and procedures as well as client requirements, including but not limited to the EU PRAG guidelines;
• Support to the identification and mobilization of long- and short-term experts and planned consultancy missions in close cooperation with GIZ's recruitment team;
• Preparation, review, and quality assurance of project reports and deliverables;
• Project management and administration in accordance with GIZ and client policies and procedures;
• Management of core project processes such as planning, financial steering and procurement in close coordination with core process support teams in Ethiopia and Germany;
• Knowledge management and development of project implementation strategies;
• Management of relationships and communications with clients, partners, and experts.
